<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>CSS Box Model Example</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .box {
      background-color: #e3f2fd;   /* Light blue background */
      border: 3px solid #1565c0;   /* Blue border */
      padding: 20px;               /* Space inside the box */
      margin: 20px;                /* Space outside the box */
      width: 300px;
    }

    .box h2 {
      margin-top: 0;               /* Remove default top margin */
      color: #1565c0;
    }

    .box p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>CSS Box Model Demo</h1>
  <p>The box model consists of <strong>margin</strong>, <strong>border</strong>, <strong>padding</strong>, and <strong>content</strong>. Below is an example:</p>

  <!-- Box Example -->
  <div class="box">
    <h2>Box Title</h2>
    <p>This box has a blue border, light blue background, padding inside, and margin outside.</p>
  </div>

  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2026 Box Model Webpage</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
